  "text": "Ϫ/Ϫ mice as it relates to glucose homeostasis and insulin tolerance. Note that this occurs in the presence of different abnormalities in glucose disposal in tibialis anterior and liver but similarly impaired glucose uptake in gastrocnemius of AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ and AS160 Ϫ/Ϫ /Tbc1d1 Ϫ/Ϫ mice ( Fig. 5 ) [CITATION_1] . A key role for AS160 in the regulation of glucose homeostasis is consistent with studies in humans with AS160 truncation mutations [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Human carriers of such mutations exhibit strikingly similar defects to those of AS160-deficient mice: impaired glucose tolerance, peripheral insulin resistance consistent with impaired glucose uptake in skeletal muscle, decreased fasting blood glucose, and decreased GLUT4 expression in skeletal muscle concomitant with drastically increased incidence of type 2 diabetes [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
